stream
q
/Tx BMC 
q
2 1 489.3312 305.999 re
W
BT
/HeBo 9.0 Tf 0 g
2 300.341 Td
(This SAR is being filed regarding suspicious activity involving Acme LLC, an import/export business, which was discovered on June 25, 2024. The activity raised suspicion due to unusual cash patterns and multiple day deposits that appeared to be structured to evade reporting requirements. Between May 1, 2024, and May 15, 2024, the subject engaged in multiple cash deposits and funds transfers totaling $19,500.50, with transactions that included cash deposits shortly after large withdrawals and wire transfers to unrelated third parties without clear business relationships. Supporting documentation includes transaction records detailing cash deposits and funds transfers, with specific transactions noted: a cash deposit of $4,500.50 on May 2, 2024, followed by a funds transfer of $5,000.00 on May 5, 2024, and additional cash withdrawals and transfers on subsequent dates. The subject declined to explain the large cash deposits when questioned. The suspicious activity is not isolated, as it relates to prior SAR filings, and there is an adverse media report indicating that the subject is under investigation. The financial institution, Example Community Bank, located in Dallas, NY, has retained all records related to this SAR for five years. Further investigation is recommended to assist law enforcement in understanding the context and purpose of these transactions.) Tj
ET
Q
EMC
Q

endstream
